sql:
SELECT reel_numbers
FROM microfilms
WHERE digitization_status = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS digitized_reel_count
FROM microfilms
WHERE digitization_status = 1;

external_knowledge:
- The digitization status of 1 implies that the microfilm has been digitized; 
- The start_date and end_date refer to the period of the archival series; 
- The year 1940 is likely a significant date in the context of the archival series.

- Frequently accessed microfilm reels are those with the highest access count within the given time period (2023); 
- The access duration is the total time spent accessing each microfilm reel; 
- The curator's name is the full name of the person responsible for the series that the microfilm reel belongs to.
